<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Armstrong</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-06-02"><hi rend="italic">June 2, 1896</hi></date>.
                                (Received June 15.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 528.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your No. 505, of the 13th ultimo, to Minister Taylor,
                            relative to the arrest of William A. Glean and his brother, Lewis N.
                            Glean, citizens of the United States, by the Spanish military
                            authorities at Sagua la Grande, Cuba, and to inform you that the case
                            has been duly presented to the Spanish Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">H. Clay Armstrong</hi>, Jr.,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires ad
                            interim.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>